RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $31,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WALKTHELINE away well, stalked the early pacesetters from the rail, was set down at the top of the lane, gained the lead with a furlong remaining, and drove clear. CREDIBILITY chased five wide in the final turn, rallied through the stretch, and edged away late to secure place. BOSS MAN CAN hurried to the front, set a pressed pace inside of WEDGE POND, and lacked the late rally required. WEDGE POND pressed the early pace three to four wide and tired in the stretch. SPORTSCARR trailed throughout.

Claiming Price $17,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,00 0.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOHAMAD raced three wide into the opening turn, stalked the pace from the rail, shifted out to the two path, ran down the leader mid-stretch and won driving. LIL ZAPPER vied for the early lead, lead the way through the far turn, and lacked the rally needed late. LAHUN stalked the pace three to four wide, rallied outside of FROSTEDBIRD, and inched clear to secure show. MUDINATOR broke slow, raced in close quarters entering the opening turn, and offered a late bid. FROSTEDBIRD pressed the pace early, rallied between rivals into the stretch and gave way late. SMART CAT checked out of tight quarters in the far turn and finished evenly. CARAVAN PRINCE failed to threaten. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of SMART CAT against the rider of MUDINATOR and MOHAMED alleging interference entering the opening turn. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 7 5F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 35000. FOR ALBERTA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG BAD INTAGLIO sat in striking range in the four path, drifted in under right-handed urging, steered out sharply, and closed steadily to score the win in a multi-horse scramble to the wire. ROUGH CUSTOMER chased inside, gained closer order into the stretch, and closed gamely deep stretch. KISS ME HELLO sent for speed inside, drifted in entering the opening turn, found the front in the final turn, responded to a looming threat into the stretch, and was run down. PACHECO checked hard out of tight quarters, chased hard entering the stretch, and just missed after a determined effort. OUR SUNSHINE raced four wide into the opening turn under a snug hold, and closed gradually under steady urging. MAMA'S PROUD JOKE saved inside, and lodged a mild late bid. VANTASTICCANAVERAL settled outside, drifted in and came up empty in the drive. BUSTER BRADY outsprinted in the turn, chased KISS ME HELLO at the head of the lane, and wilted abruptly late stretch. H K RAPPER chased to no avail. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of PACHECO against the rider of KISS ME HELLO alleging interference into the opening turn was upheld. KISS ME HELLO wsa disqualified and placed fourth for interference to PACHECO.

ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed, drifted in, lead, run down
